  "page": "Nettles/Theories",
  "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table align=\"right\" width=\"180px\" style=\"float:right; margin: 0em 0em 1em 1em;\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th style=\"text-align: center; background-color:#c2c2c2; font-size:12px; -moz-border-radius-topleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-topright:10px;\">&#160;Theories&#160;may&#160;be&#160;removed&#160;if&#160;...&#160;\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"font-size:11px; text-align: left; background-color:#eeeeee; font-weight:lighter;-moz-border-radius-bottomleft:10px;-moz-border-radius-bottomright:10px;padding-right: 1em; padding-left: .5em; padding-right: .5em;\">\n<ol><li>Stated as questions or possibilities.</li>\n<li>More appropriate for another article.</li>\n<li>Illogical or previously disproven.</li>\n<li>Proven by canon source, and moved to main page.</li>\n<li>Speculative and lacking any evidence to support arguments.</li>\n<li>Responding to another theory (use <a href=\"/index.php?title=Talk:Nettles/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Talk:Nettles/Theories (page does not exist)\">discussion page</a> instead).</li></ol>\n<dl><dd><ul><li><small>This does not include responses that are also standalone theories.</small></li>\n<li><small>Usage of an indented bullet does not imply the statement is a response.</small></li></ul></dd></dl>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>It has been speculated that <a href=\"/index.php/Nettles\" title=\"Nettles\">Nettles</a>, the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonrider\" title=\"Dragonrider\">rider</a> of the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragon\" title=\"Dragon\">dragon</a> <a href=\"/index.php/Sheepstealer\" title=\"Sheepstealer\">Sheepstealer</a> and allegedly <a href=\"/index.php/Daemon_Targaryen\" title=\"Daemon Targaryen\">Daemon Targaryen</a>'s <a href=\"/index.php/Paramour\" title=\"Paramour\">paramour</a> during the <a href=\"/index.php/Dance_of_the_Dragons\" title=\"Dance of the Dragons\">Dance of the Dragons</a>, was actually a secret bastard daughter of Daemon instead of his lover.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Supporting_evidence\">Supporting evidence</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Nettles/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Supporting evidence\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The following pieces of information can be seen as evidence:\n</p>\n<ul><li>According to Maester <a href=\"/index.php/Norren_(House_Mooton)\" title=\"Norren (House Mooton)\">Norren</a>, who watched the prince and the <a href=\"/index.php/Dragonseed\" title=\"Dragonseed\">dragonseed</a> closely, and recorded their relationship in his <i><a href=\"/index.php/Chronicles_of_Maidenpool\" title=\"Chronicles of Maidenpool\">Chronicles of Maidenpool</a></i>, Daemon doted on Nettles \"as a man might dote upon his daughter\"; in particular, Norren describes Daemon teaching Nettles common courtesies and giving her fine gifts, as well as showing her how to wash herself properly. Additionally, Norren calls the dragonseed Daemon's \"<a href=\"/index.php/Bastard\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Bastard\">bastard</a> girl\", which could mean Nettles is his illegitimate child.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>On the contrary, the two sources claiming that Nettles was Daemon's lover are Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Mysaria\" title=\"Mysaria\">Mysaria</a>, once Daemon's paramour, and the fool <a href=\"/index.php/Mushroom\" title=\"Mushroom\">Mushroom</a>, who were not with the prince and the dragonseed at the time the rumors were raised, and whose veracity is debatable. Mushroom's <i>Testimony</i> is known to be filled with tales of plots, murders, trysts, debaucheries, and many other salacious claims. The <a href=\"/index.php/Mistress_of_whisperers\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Mistress of whisperers\">mistress of whisperers</a>' loyalty to <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaenyra_Targaryen\" title=\"Rhaenyra Targaryen\">Rhaenyra Targaryen</a> is questionable, since Mysaria fed the queen's distrust of <a href=\"/index.php/House_Velaryon\" title=\"House Velaryon\">House Velaryon</a>, her most powerful allies, and played a role in <a href=\"/index.php/Helaena_Targaryen\" title=\"Helaena Targaryen\">Helaena Targaryen</a>'s suicide.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;N 1&#93;</a></sup> It is therefore possible that Mysaria accused Nettles of being Daemon's lover to keep the prince and the queen apart. About that, it is suggested Daemon understood that Rhaenyra's death sentence for Nettles was the result of sabotage by the White Worm, since he called the queen's decree \"A queen’s words, a whore’s work.\"<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>It is hinted that Daemon had at least a bastard child before <a href=\"/index.php/Baela_Targaryen\" title=\"Baela Targaryen\">Baela</a> and <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a> were born: \"In <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_116_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">116&#160;AC</a>, in the <a href=\"/index.php/Free_City\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Free City\">Free City</a> of <a href=\"/index.php/Pentos\" title=\"Pentos\">Pentos</a>, Lady <a href=\"/index.php/Laena_Velaryon\" title=\"Laena Velaryon\">Laena</a> gave birth to twin daughters, Prince Daemon’s first trueborn children.\" Nettles was born on <a href=\"/index.php/Driftmark\" title=\"Driftmark\">Driftmark</a> in <a href=\"/index.php/Years_after_Aegon%27s_Conquest#Year_113_After_the_Conquest\" title=\"Years after Aegon&#39;s Conquest\">113&#160;AC</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Counting living and stillborn children, Daemon had a total of six official children, three sons and three daughters, just like six of the seven <a href=\"/index.php/New_gods\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"New gods\">new gods</a>. If Nettles were Daemon's bastard daughter, she would correspond to the seventh god, the <a href=\"/index.php/Stranger_(the_Seven)\" title=\"Stranger (the Seven)\">Stranger</a>. Just like the Stranger represents death and the unknown, Nettles would be the prince's secret child, as well as the cause of his demise.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>Nettles may have been inspired by Nettle Farseer, a character from the <i><a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Farseer_trilogy\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Farseer trilogy\">Farseer trilogy</a></i>, a series of fantasy novels by American author <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robin_Hobb\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"w:Robin Hobb\">Robin Hobb</a>. <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> knows Hobb and praised her body of work. Nettle Farseer is the illegitimate daughter of FitzChivalry Farseer, the main protagonist of the series.<sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup></li>\n<li>In the television adaptation <i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>, Nettles is merged with <a href=\"/index.php/Rhaena_Targaryen_(daughter_of_Daemon)\" title=\"Rhaena Targaryen (daughter of Daemon)\">Rhaena Targaryen</a>, which means that, at least in the show canon, the rider of Sheepstealer is indeed one of Daemon's daughters.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e08.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rhbohotds02e08.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Notes\">Notes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Nettles/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: Notes\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Septon <a href=\"/index.php/Eustace_(Dance_of_the_Dragons)\" title=\"Eustace (Dance of the Dragons)\">Eustace</a> suggested the queen killed herself after Mysaria told her of the death of her son <a href=\"/index.php/Maelor_Targaryen\" title=\"Maelor Targaryen\">Maelor</a> and the gruesome manner it had happened.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Rfab17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Rfab17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> In a now deleted blog post, <a href=\"/index.php/George_R._R._Martin\" title=\"George R. R. Martin\">George R. R. Martin</a> confirmed that hearing of Maelor's death was what drove Helaena to commit suicide, out of grief and guilt.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Nettles/Theories&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" class=\"tw-editsection-onhover\" title=\"Edit section: References\"><span class=\"glyphicon glyphicon-pencil\"></span> </a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"references-small\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_triumphant.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_1-2\">1.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Triumphant.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfab17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfab17.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_2-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Overthrown.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-3\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-3\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_a_Blog\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Not a Blog\">Not a Blog</a>: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://web.archive.org/web/20240904154210/https://georgerrmartin.com/notablog/2024/09/04/beware-the-butterflies/\">Beware the Butterflies</a>. George R. R. Martin (September 4, 2024). Archived and retrieved September 4, 2024.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-0\">4.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-1\">4.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabheirs_of_the_dragon_-_a_question_of_succession.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_5-2\">4.2</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, Heirs of the Dragon - A Question of Succession.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rfabthe_dying_of_the_dragons_-_rhaenyra_overthrown.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_6-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/Fire_%26_Blood\" title=\"Fire &amp; Blood\">Fire &amp; Blood</a></i>, The Dying of the Dragons - Rhaenyra Overthrown.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/index.php/Not_a_Blog\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Not a Blog\">Not a Blog</a>: <a class=\"external text\" href=\"https://georgerrmartin.com/notablog/2021/07/30/lords-of-fantasy/\">Lords of Fantasy</a> (July 30, 2021)</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Robin Hobb's Realm of the Elderlings Wiki: <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://robinhobbelderlings.fandom.com/wiki/Nettle_Farseer\">Nettle Farseer</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-Rhbohotds02e08.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-Rhbohotds02e08.7B.7B.7B3.7D.7D.7D.7B.7B.7B4.7D.7D.7D_9-0\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><i><a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon\" title=\"House of the Dragon\">House of the Dragon</a></i>, <a href=\"/index.php/House_of_the_Dragon_-_Season_2\" title=\"House of the Dragon - Season 2\">Season 2</a>, \"<a href=\"/index.php/The_Queen_Who_Ever_Was\" title=\"The Queen Who Ever Was\">The Queen Who Ever Was</a>\".</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260404161856\nCache expiry: 1209600\nDynamic content: false\nCPU time usage: 0.047 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.071 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 986/1000000\nPreprocessor generated node count: 9253/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 4921/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 2154/2097152 byt